{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017pvKVwoDfDdxXg41Eo6ZAP","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 14-4: Observability Backend Choice (Victoria vs ELK vs Remote)\n     2→\n     3→## Status: backlog\n     4→\n     5→## Story\n     6→\n     7→As a developer initializing codeharness,\n     8→I want to choose my observability backend and provide remote endpoints,\n     9→So that I'm not locked into VictoriaMetrics with hardcoded ports.\n    10→\n    11→## Acceptance Criteria\n    12→\n    13→- [ ] AC1: Given `codeharness init --observability-backend elk`, when init runs, then state stores `otlp.backend: 'elk'` and ELK compose is used <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    14→- [ ] AC2: Given `codeharness init --otel-endpoint https://remote:4318 --logs-url https://remote:9200`, when init runs, then no local Docker stack is started and state stores remote endpoints <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    15→- [ ] AC3: Given `otlp.backend` is `'elk'`, when `codeharness status --check-docker` runs, then it checks ELK containers (not Victoria) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    16→\n    17→## Technical Notes\n    18→\n    19→**Decision 5 (Observability Backend Choice).** Currently VictoriaMetrics is hardcoded everywhere with hardcoded ports.\n    20→\n    21→### State Schema\n    22→\n    23→Add to `codeharness.local.md` YAML frontmatter (managed by `src/lib/state.ts`):\n    24→\n    25→```typescript\n    26→interface OtlpConfig {\n    27→  enabled: boolean;\n    28→  backend: 'victoria' | 'elk' | 'none';\n    29→  mode: 'local-shared' | 'remote';\n    30→  endpoints: {\n    31→    otel: string;     // OTLP collector (default: http://localhost:4318)\n    32→    logs: string;     // Log query API (Victoria: :9428, ELK: :9200)\n    33→    metrics: string;  // Metric query API (Victoria: :8428, ELK: :9200)\n    34→    traces: string;   // Trace query API (Victoria: :16686)\n    35→  };\n    36→  service_name: string;\n    37→}\n    38→```\n    39→\n    40→### ObservabilityBackend Interface\n    41→\n    42→From architecture-v3.md:\n    43→```typescript\n    44→interface ObservabilityBackend {\n    45→  buildLogQuery(service: string, timeRange: string): string;\n    46→  buildMetricQuery(service: string, metric: string): string;\n    47→  buildTraceQuery(service: string, limit: number): string;\n    48→  getComposeFile(): string;\n    49→  getHealthCheck(): HealthCheckResult;\n    50→}\n    51→```\n    52→\n    53→Two implementations: `VictoriaBackend` (existing, extract from current code) and `ElkBackend` (new). These live in `src/lib/observability/backends.ts` (after Epic 12) or `src/modules/infra/` for now.\n    54→\n    55→Existing implementations: `src/modules/infra/victoria-backend.ts` and `src/modules/infra/opensearch-backend.ts` already exist. Refactor to implement the unified `ObservabilityBackend` interface.\n    56→\n    57→### Init Flow Changes\n    58→\n    59→Modify `src/commands/init.ts` and `src/modules/infra/init-project.ts`:\n    60→- Add `--observability-backend <victoria|elk|none>` CLI option\n    61→- Add `--otel-endpoint`, `--logs-url`, `--metrics-url`, `--traces-url` for remote mode\n    62→- If remote endpoints provided, set `mode: 'remote'`, skip Docker compose\n    63→- Store selection in state\n    64→\n    65→### Docker Health Dispatch\n    66→\n    67→Modify `src/commands/status.ts` (or `src/modules/status/` after Epic 12) to dispatch health checks based on `state.otlp.backend`:\n    68→- `victoria` -> check VictoriaMetrics containers\n    69→- `elk` -> check Elasticsearch + Kibana containers\n    70→- `none` -> skip Docker checks\n    71→- Remote mode -> ping endpoints instead of checking containers\n    72→\n    73→### Compose Templates\n    74→\n    75→`templates/compose/victoria.yml` and `templates/compose/elk.yml` should be selected based on backend choice. Currently only Victoria compose exists.\n    76→\n    77→## Files to Change\n    78→\n    79→- `src/lib/state.ts` — Update `OtlpConfig` type to include `backend`, `mode`, `endpoints` fields\n    80→- `src/types/state.ts` — Add `ObservabilityBackend` interface type\n    81→- `src/modules/infra/victoria-backend.ts` — Refactor to implement `ObservabilityBackend` interface\n    82→- `src/modules/infra/opensearch-backend.ts` — Refactor to implement `ObservabilityBackend` interface as ELK backend\n    83→- `src/commands/init.ts` — Add `--observability-backend`, `--otel-endpoint`, `--logs-url` options\n    84→- `src/modules/infra/init-project.ts` — Handle backend selection and remote endpoint storage\n    85→- `src/modules/infra/docker-setup.ts` — Select compose file based on backend choice\n    86→- `src/commands/status.ts` — Dispatch Docker health checks based on `state.otlp.backend`\n    87→- `templates/compose/elk.yml` — Create. ELK stack Docker Compose configuration\n    88→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_011GhyUaMpB5RRP9ifchfuED","session_id":"790cd04c-5c91-45bb-998d-78a56b65af9a","uuid":"c62d3acf-80da-40a6-8b7e-dda5c907863a","timestamp":"2026-03-24T23:02:31.359Z"}
