{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_015GxeYPSr7TSpN6AGaTVtHB","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"790cd04c-5c91-45bb-998d-78a56b65af9a","uuid":"d3b40b21-8386-460a-8d85-eb9c81e77ced","timestamp":"2026-03-24T23:06:12.138Z","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","oldString":"- Architecture concern: docker --version vs docker info gap means AC#1 may not catch daemon-stopped-but-CLI-installed case. Pre-existing design decision.","newString":"- Architecture concern: docker --version vs docker info gap means AC#1 may not catch daemon-stopped-but-CLI-installed case. Pre-existing design decision.\n\n### 14-4-observability-backend-choice — create-story (2026-03-25T03:05:00Z)\n\n- Risk: docker-setup.ts at 299 lines — adding backend-aware compose selection will push past 300-line limit\n- Risk: formatters.ts at 574 lines (pre-existing violation) — any additions worsen it\n- Risk: state.ts at 293 lines — adding backend field + migration pushes close to 300\n- Observation: Epic says \"ELK\" but code uses OpenSearchBackend (OpenSearch = OSS Elasticsearch fork). User-facing `--observability-backend elk` maps to internal 'opensearch'. Documented in anti-patterns.\n- Observation: Codebase well-prepared — ObservabilityBackend interface, VictoriaBackend, OpenSearchBackend all exist. Main gap is CLI selector and backend-aware health check dispatch.","originalFile":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-25\n\n### 14-1-retro-to-sprint-pipeline-epic-td — code-review (2026-03-25T01:59:00Z)\n\n- HIGH (fixed): `generateSlug('')` returns `''`, creating malformed TD story keys\n- HIGH (fixed): `backlogAppended` reports items as persisted when `projectRoot` is omitted\n- HIGH (fixed): `wordOverlap` exceeds 1.0 with duplicate words, breaking dedup contract\n- MEDIUM (fixed): Missing test for no-projectRoot path\n- LOW (unfixed): `getExistingTdTitles` reconstructs titles from slugs, losing fidelity\n- LOW (unfixed): `createTdStory` implicitly creates `epic-TD` via spread+override without `ensureEpicTd` call\n- Coverage gap: No test for `appendToBacklogFile` append-to-existing path or error handling\n- Architecture: state.ts at 543 lines exceeds 300-line limit (pre-existing)\n\n### 14-1-retro-to-sprint-pipeline-epic-td — verification (2026-03-25T02:05:00Z)\n\n- AGENTS.md for src/lib was stale — missing retro-to-sprint.ts entry. Fixed.\n- Disk space critically low (45MB free) — BATS tests failed with \"No space left on device\". Cleared npm cache (2.2GB) to free space.\n- All 10 ACs passed unit-testable verification with direct CLI checks\n- Pre-existing files (state.ts at 543 lines, sprint-yaml.test.ts at 388 lines) exceed 300-line limit but were over before this story\n\n### 14-2-tech-debt-gate-story-selection — create-story (2026-03-25T02:10:00Z)\n\n- Risk: selector.test.ts at 274 lines — adding ~80 lines of new tests may push past 300-line limit, conflicting with AC 9\n- Observation: Original epic had only 2 ACs; expanded to 9 to cover edge cases. Original ACs were underspecified about Tier D gate constraint.\n- Observation: Implementation is ~3 lines in sort comparator. Test changes are the bulk of work.\n\n### 14-2-tech-debt-gate-story-selection — dev-story (2026-03-25T02:20:00Z)\n\nNo issues reported. All 11 tasks completed cleanly. 4 lines added to selector.ts, 7 test cases added via it.each. Build, vitest (3664 tests), and BATS (307 tests) all pass.\n\n### 14-2-tech-debt-gate-story-selection — code-review (2026-03-25T02:27:00Z)\n\n- MEDIUM (fixed): AGENTS.md missing TD gate documentation\n- MEDIUM (fixed): Test shorthand variables polluted scope; replaced with typed it.each\n- MEDIUM (fixed): Added case-sensitivity and ready-status test cases (2 new tests, total 3666)\n- LOW (unfixed): selector.ts line 103 comment lacks Decision 6c reference\n- LOW (unfixed): keyToTitle() lowercases \"TD\" to \"Td\" — pre-existing\n- Architecture note: TD gate relies on naming convention (TD- prefix) not structured metadata — accepted tradeoff per Decision 6c\n\n### 14-3-docker-precheck-orphan-cleanup — create-story (2026-03-25T02:42:00Z)\n\n- Risk: run.ts at 287 lines — adding Docker pre-check + orphan cleanup (~12 lines) brings it to ~299. Any additional pre-flight gates will breach 300-line limit.\n- Observation: duplicate cleanup functions — `cleanupStaleContainers()` in verify/env.ts and `cleanupContainers()` in infra/container-cleanup.ts overlap for verify containers. Harmless but is tech debt.\n- Observation: docker/cleanup.ts is a dead stub — `cleanupOrphanedContainers()` always returns 0. Real logic lives in infra module.\n\n### 14-3-docker-precheck-orphan-cleanup — dev-story (2026-03-25T02:48:00Z)\n\n- Code quality concern: run.ts at exactly 300 lines — zero margin. Future additions require extracting helpers.\n- Observation: run.test.ts at 947 lines, far exceeding 300-line limit. AC#9 says no modified file exceeds 300 lines but test files routinely exceed. Followed existing pattern.\n- Observation: docker/cleanup.ts stub tests fully rewritten — implementation changed from no-op to delegation.\n\n### 14-3-docker-precheck-orphan-cleanup — code-review (2026-03-25T02:52:00Z)\n\n- MEDIUM (fixed): AGENTS.md files for infra and commands modules were stale\n- LOW (unfixed): `isDockerAvailable()` uses `docker --version` not `docker info` — only checks CLI presence, not daemon. Pre-existing across codebase.\n- LOW (unfixed): Double `isDockerAvailable()` call — run.ts checks, then cleanupContainers() checks again. Harmless overhead.\n- Architecture concern: docker --version vs docker info gap means AC#1 may not catch daemon-stopped-but-CLI-installed case. Pre-existing design decision.\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":55,"oldLines":3,"newStart":55,"newLines":11,"lines":[" - LOW (unfixed): `isDockerAvailable()` uses `docker --version` not `docker info` — only checks CLI presence, not daemon. Pre-existing across codebase."," - LOW (unfixed): Double `isDockerAvailable()` call — run.ts checks, then cleanupContainers() checks again. Harmless overhead."," - Architecture concern: docker --version vs docker info gap means AC#1 may not catch daemon-stopped-but-CLI-installed case. Pre-existing design decision.","+","+### 14-4-observability-backend-choice — create-story (2026-03-25T03:05:00Z)","+","+- Risk: docker-setup.ts at 299 lines — adding backend-aware compose selection will push past 300-line limit","+- Risk: formatters.ts at 574 lines (pre-existing violation) — any additions worsen it","+- Risk: state.ts at 293 lines — adding backend field + migration pushes close to 300","+- Observation: Epic says \"ELK\" but code uses OpenSearchBackend (OpenSearch = OSS Elasticsearch fork). User-facing `--observability-backend elk` maps to internal 'opensearch'. Documented in anti-patterns.","+- Observation: Codebase well-prepared — ObservabilityBackend interface, VictoriaBackend, OpenSearchBackend all exist. Main gap is CLI selector and backend-aware health check dispatch."]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
