tests pass, 140 test files, zero failures\n- `npm test` (BATS) -- 307 tests pass\n- All files under 300-line limit (except `formatters.ts` which is exempt per AC 10)\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **`docker-setup.ts` at 300 lines**: Pre-story it was at 299. Added 1 effective line (the backend/compose selection). Now at exactly 300. Any future changes to this file will need extraction or refactoring.\n- **`formatters.ts` grew from 574 to 597**: This is a pre-existing violation that grew by 23 lines. The backend-aware checks in three separate functions (`handleDockerCheck`, `handleFullStatus`, `handleHealthCheck`, `handleFullStatusJson`) each needed `backend === 'none'` guards. A future refactoring story should extract shared backend-dispatch logic.\n- **Missing `getElkComposeFilePath` mock caused silent failure**: The init-project test file's mock for `stack-path.js` didn't include the new export. This caused `setupDocker` to throw inside its try/catch, silently swallowing the error and returning a fail result without writing state. Fixed by adding the mock and also adding an explicit `writeState` call before Docker setup to persist the backend choice.\n- **`writeState` added before Docker setup (init-project.ts line 191)**: This is a defensive write to ensure `otlp.backend` persists even if Docker setup fails. It adds a small I/O overhead (one extra write) but prevents data loss. The existing pattern relied on Docker setup to write the final state, which was fragile.\n- **ELK compose endpoints not backend-specific**: The `DEFAULT_ENDPOINTS` used in `handleDockerCheck` show Victoria ports (9428, 8428, 16686) even for the ELK backend. OpenSearch uses different ports (9200 for logs/search, 5601 for dashboards). This is a known gap -- the endpoints module would need ELK-specific defaults. Not addressed because it was not in the ACs."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a3780ccc0d09e87d2 (use SendMessage with to: 'a3780ccc0d09e87d2' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 