{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01GpK9oePiEzztj9MzYwusCN","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 14-4: Observability Backend Choice (Victoria vs ELK vs Remote)\n     2→\n     3→Status: review\n     4→\n     5→<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n     6→\n     7→## Story\n     8→\n     9→As a developer initializing codeharness,\n    10→I want to choose my observability backend and provide remote endpoints,\n    11→So that I'm not locked into VictoriaMetrics with hardcoded ports.\n    12→\n    13→## Acceptance Criteria\n    14→\n    15→1. Given `codeharness init --observability-backend elk`, when init runs, then state stores `otlp.backend: 'elk'` and the OpenSearch/ELK compose template is used instead of the Victoria compose template <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    16→2. Given `codeharness init --observability-backend victoria` (or no flag), when init runs, then state stores `otlp.backend: 'victoria'` and the existing Victoria compose is used (backward compatible default) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    17→3. Given `codeharness init --otel-endpoint https://remote:4318 --logs-url https://remote:9200`, when init runs, then no local Docker stack is started and state stores remote endpoints with `otlp.mode: 'remote-direct'` or `'remote-routed'` <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    18→4. Given `otlp.backend` is `'elk'`, when `codeharness status --check-docker` runs, then it checks OpenSearch/ELK containers (not Victoria containers) and reports their health <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    19→5. Given `otlp.backend` is `'none'`, when `codeharness status --check-docker` runs, then Docker health checks are skipped with an informational message <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    20→6. Given `codeharness init --observability-backend none`, when init runs, then no Docker compose is started, `otlp.enabled` is `false`, and OTLP instrumentation is skipped <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    21→7. Given the `ObservabilityBackend` interface already exists in `src/types/observability.ts`, when both `VictoriaBackend` and `OpenSearchBackend` are inspected, then both implement the same interface (already the case; this AC validates no regression) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    22→8. Given `npm run build` runs after all changes, then TypeScript compilation succeeds with zero errors <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    23→9. Given `npm test` runs after all changes, then all existing tests pass with zero regressions <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    24→10. Given no new file created for this story exceeds 300 lines, when line count is checked, then all modified files remain under 300 lines (note: `formatters.ts` is already at 574 lines pre-story; it is exempt from this AC but should not grow further) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    25→\n    26→## Tasks / Subtasks\n    27→\n    28→- [x] Task 1 (AC: 1, 2, 6): Add `--observability-backend` CLI option to `init.ts`\n    29→  - [x]Add `.option('--observability-backend <type>', 'Observability backend: victoria, elk, or none (default: victoria)')` to the init command\n    30→  - [x]Pass the value through `InitOptions` to `initProject()`\n    31→\n    32→- [x] Task 2 (AC: 1, 2, 6): Update `InitOptions` in `src/modules/infra/types.ts`\n    33→  - [x]Add `observabilityBackend?: 'victoria' | 'elk' | 'none'` to `InitOptions`\n    34→\n    35→- [x] Task 3 (AC: 1, 2, 6): Update `HarnessState.otlp` in `src/lib/state.ts`\n    36→  - [x]Add `backend?: 'victoria' | 'elk' | 'none'` field to the `otlp` interface\n    37→  - [x]Ensure `getDefaultState()` sets `backend: 'victoria'` as default\n    38→  - [x]Ensure `migrateState()` backfills `backend: 'victoria'` for existing states without the field\n    39→\n    40→- [x] Task 4 (AC: 1, 2, 6): Update `initProjectInner()` in `src/modules/infra/init-project.ts`\n    41→  - [x]Read `opts.observabilityBackend` and store it in `state.otlp.backend`\n    42→  - [x]If `observabilityBackend === 'none'`, skip OTLP instrumentation and Docker setup (similar to `--no-observability` but persisted in state)\n    43→  - [x]If `observabilityBackend === 'elk'`, the Docker setup should use OpenSearch compose (or delegate to `docker-setup.ts`)\n    44→\n    45→- [x] Task 5 (AC: 1, 2): Update `docker-setup.ts` to select compose based on backend\n    46→  - [x]In `handleLocalShared()`, check `state.otlp.backend` to determine which compose file to use\n    47→  - [x]Victoria -> existing `docker-compose.harness.yml` (default)\n    48→  - [x]ELK -> an ELK/OpenSearch compose file (create `templates/docker-compose.elk.yml` or equivalent)\n    49→  - [x]Ensure the compose file path is stored correctly in state\n    50→\n    51→- [x] Task 6 (AC: 4, 5): Update `handleDockerCheck()` in `src/modules/status/formatters.ts`\n    52→  - [x]Read `state.otlp?.backend` alongside `state.otlp?.mode`\n    53→  - [x]If `backend === 'none'`: output `[INFO] Observability disabled — no Docker check needed` and return early\n    54→  - [x]If `backend === 'elk'` and mode is `local-shared`: check OpenSearch containers instead of Victoria containers\n    55→  - [x]If `backend === 'victoria'` (or unset, for backward compat): existing Victoria check (no change)\n    56→\n    57→- [x] Task 7 (AC: 4): Update `handleFullStatus()` Docker section in `formatters.ts`\n    58→  - [x]For `backend === 'elk'` in `local-shared` mode, display OpenSearch health instead of Victoria\n    59→  - [x]For `backend === 'none'`, display `Docker: disabled (observability off)`\n    60→\n    61→- [x] Task 8 (AC: 1): Create `templates/docker-compose.elk.yml`\n    62→  - [x]OpenSearch + OpenSearch Dashboards + OTel Collector compose definition\n    63→  - [x]Use sensible defaults (single-node, security disabled for local dev)\n    64→  - [x]Expose standard ports (9200 for OpenSearch, 5601 for Dashboards, 4317/4318 for OTLP)\n    65→\n    66→- [x] Task 9 (AC: 7): Verify `ObservabilityBackend` interface conformance\n    67→  - [x]Verify `VictoriaBackend` and `OpenSearchBackend` both already implement `ObservabilityBackend`\n    68→  - [x]No code changes expected — just verification\n    69→\n    70→- [x] Task 10 (AC: 1, 2, 4, 6): Add unit tests\n    71→  - [x]Test: init with `--observability-backend elk` -> state stores `otlp.backend: 'elk'`\n    72→  - [x]Test: init with `--observability-backend victoria` -> state stores `otlp.backend: 'victoria'`\n    73→  - [x]Test: init with `--observability-backend none` -> state stores `otlp.backend: 'none'`, no Docker\n    74→  - [x]Test: init with no flag -> backward compat default `'victoria'`\n    75→  - [x]Test: `handleDockerCheck` with `backend: 'elk'` -> checks OpenSearch health\n    76→  - [x]Test: `handleDockerCheck` with `backend: 'none'` -> skips check\n    77→\n    78→- [x] Task 11 (AC: 3): Verify remote endpoint flow still works with backend field\n    79→  - [x]Test: `--otel-endpoint` with `--observability-backend elk` -> remote mode with elk backend\n    80→  - [x]Ensure no regression in existing remote endpoint tests\n    81→\n    82→- [x] Task 12 (AC: 8): Run `npm run build` — TypeScript compilation succeeds\n    83→- [x] Task 13 (AC: 9): Run `npm test` — all existing tests pass, zero regressions\n    84→- [x] Task 14 (AC: 10): Verify all modified files are under 300 lines (exempt: `formatters.ts` at 574 pre-story)\n    85→\n    86→## Dev Notes\n    87→\n    88→### Architecture Compliance\n    89→\n    90→- **Decision 5 (Observability Backend Choice):** This story implements the backend selection mechanism. The architecture specifies Victoria vs ELK vs None, with remote endpoints as an orthogonal axis. The `ObservabilityBackend` interface (`src/types/observability.ts`) already exists with `VictoriaBackend` and `OpenSearchBackend` implementations — no new interface needed.\n    91→- **Decision 7 (300-line limit, NFR5):** `formatters.ts` is already at 574 lines — this is a pre-existing violation from Epic 12 restructuring. This story should not increase it. `docker-setup.ts` is at 299 lines — budget is extremely tight.\n    92→\n    93→### Implementation Guidance\n    94→\n    95→#### Current State Assessment\n    96→\n    97→The codebase is **partially ready** for this story. Key observations:\n    98→\n    99→1. **`ObservabilityBackend` interface** already exists at `src/types/observability.ts:100-106` with `queryLogs`, `queryMetrics`, `queryTraces`, `healthCheck` methods.\n   100→2. **`VictoriaBackend`** (267 lines) at `src/modules/infra/victoria-backend.ts` — fully implemented.\n   101→3. **`OpenSearchBackend`** (183 lines) at `src/modules/infra/opensearch-backend.ts` — fully implemented. This IS the \"ELK\" backend (OpenSearch = open-source Elasticsearch fork).\n   102→4. **Init command** already has `--otel-endpoint`, `--opensearch-url`, `--logs-url`, `--metrics-url`, `--traces-url` options.\n   103→5. **Missing:** `--observability-backend` CLI option, `otlp.backend` state field, backend-aware Docker health dispatch, ELK compose template.\n   104→\n   105→#### What to add\n   106→\n   107→**`src/commands/init.ts`** — Add one CLI option:\n   108→```typescript\n   109→.option('--observability-backend <type>', 'Observability backend: victoria, elk, or none (default: victoria)')\n   110→```\n   111→And pass it through: `observabilityBackend: options.observabilityBackend`. File is 65 lines — plenty of budget.\n   112→\n   113→**`src/modules/infra/types.ts`** — Add to `InitOptions`:\n   114→```typescript\n   115→readonly observabilityBackend?: 'victoria' | 'elk' | 'none';\n   116→```\n   117→File is 136 lines — plenty of budget.\n   118→\n   119→**`src/lib/state.ts`** — Add `backend` field to the `otlp` interface:\n   120→```typescript\n   121→backend?: 'victoria' | 'elk' | 'none';\n   122→```\n   123→In `getDefaultState()`, set `backend: 'victoria'`. In `migrateState()`, backfill for old states. File is 293 lines — tight.\n   124→\n   125→**`src/modules/infra/init-project.ts`** — In `initProjectInner()`:\n   126→- After state creation, set `state.otlp.backend = opts.observabilityBackend ?? 'victoria'`\n   127→- If `backend === 'none'`, treat like `--no-observability` (skip OTLP + Docker)\n   128→- File is 236 lines — budget OK.\n   129→\n   130→**`src/modules/infra/docker-setup.ts`** — In `handleLocalShared()`:\n   131→- Check `state.otlp?.backend` to select compose file\n   132→- `elk` -> use ELK compose path\n   133→- `victoria` (default) -> existing behavior\n   134→- File is 299 lines — effectively at limit. May need to extract a helper or accept 300.\n   135→\n   136→**`src/modules/status/formatters.ts`** — In `handleDockerCheck()` and `handleFullStatus()`:\n   137→- Read `state.otlp?.backend`\n   138→- `none` -> skip Docker checks\n   139→- `elk` -> use `OpenSearchBackend.healthCheck()` or check OpenSearch containers\n   140→- This file is already at 574 lines (pre-existing violation). Minimize additions.\n   141→\n   142→**`templates/docker-compose.elk.yml`** — New file. OpenSearch single-node setup with OTel Collector.\n   143→\n   144→#### What NOT to do\n   145→\n   146→- Do NOT create a new `ObservabilityBackend` interface — it already exists at `src/types/observability.ts`.\n   147→- Do NOT rename `OpenSearchBackend` to `ElkBackend` — OpenSearch IS the ELK replacement. The `--observability-backend elk` flag maps to OpenSearch internally.\n   148→- Do NOT add `backend` to `ObservabilityBackendType` in `observability.ts` — that type tracks implementation types (`victoria | opensearch`), not the user-facing choice. The user-facing `'elk'` maps to `'opensearch'` internally.\n   149→- Do NOT refactor `formatters.ts` to fix the 574-line violation — that's a separate tech debt story.\n   150→- Do NOT modify `docker-setup.ts` beyond what's needed — it's at 299 lines.\n   151→\n   152→### Testing Guidance\n   153→\n   154→- **Vitest** (not Jest). Use `vi.fn()`, `vi.mock()`, `vi.mocked()`.\n   155→- Imports: `import { describe, it, expect, vi } from 'vitest'`\n   156→- Existing test files to extend:\n   157→  - `src/modules/infra/__tests__/docker-setup.test.ts` — add tests for backend-aware compose selection\n   158→  - `src/modules/infra/__tests__/init-project.test.ts` — add tests for `--observability-backend` option\n   159→  - `src/modules/status/__tests__/` — add tests for backend-aware Docker check\n   160→- Mock patterns: follow existing test files' mocking approach for `readState`, Docker functions.\n   161→\n   162→### Previous Story Intelligence (14-3)\n   163→\n   164→- Story 14-3 was lean: 3 files changed, ~13 lines of new logic in `run.ts`, 1 pattern added to cleanup.\n   165→- The 300-line limit was strictly monitored. `run.ts` ended at exactly 300 lines.\n   166→- `docker-setup.ts` is at 299 lines — any addition must be minimal or extract code first.\n   167→\n   168→### Key Observations About Existing Code\n   169→\n   170→1. **`ObservabilityBackendType`** in `observability.ts` is `'victoria' | 'opensearch'` — NOT `'elk'`. The user-facing `--observability-backend elk` maps to internal `'opensearch'`.\n   171→2. **`HarnessState.otlp.mode`** already has `'local-shared' | 'remote-direct' | 'remote-routed'` — backend choice is ORTHOGONAL to mode. A user can have `backend: 'elk'` with `mode: 'local-shared'` (local Docker) or `mode: 'remote-direct'` (remote OpenSearch).\n   172→3. **`docker-setup.ts`** at 299 lines. The `handleLocalShared()` function is the main target — it currently always uses Victoria compose. Adding backend dispatch here will push the file to/past 300 lines. May need to extract the compose-file selection to a helper.\n   173→4. **No `templates/compose/` directory exists.** The compose template is at `templates/docker-compose.harness.yml` (Victoria). The ELK compose should follow the same pattern: `templates/docker-compose.elk.yml`.\n   174→5. **`formatters.ts`** is already 574 lines — a pre-existing violation. This story should add the minimum needed for backend-aware checks without growing it significantly.\n   175→\n   176→### References\n   177→\n   178→- [Source: _bmad-output/planning-artifacts/epics-architecture-v3.md lines 365-380] — Story 14-4 epic definition\n   179→- [Source: src/types/observability.ts] — ObservabilityBackend interface (already exists)\n   180→- [Source: src/modules/infra/victoria-backend.ts] — Victoria implementation (267 lines)\n   181→- [Source: src/modules/infra/opensearch-backend.ts] — OpenSearch/ELK implementation (183 lines)\n   182→- [Source: src/commands/init.ts] — Init command (65 lines) — add --observability-backend option\n   183→- [Source: src/modules/infra/init-project.ts] — Init orchestrator (236 lines) — store backend choice\n   184→- [Source: src/modules/infra/docker-setup.ts] — Docker setup (299 lines) — compose selection by backend\n   185→- [Source: src/modules/status/formatters.ts] — Status formatters (574 lines) — backend-aware health checks\n   186→- [Source: src/lib/state.ts] — State management (293 lines) — add backend field to otlp\n   187→\n   188→## Files to Change\n   189→\n   190→- `src/commands/init.ts` — Add `--observability-backend` CLI option. +3 lines. Target: ~68 lines.\n   191→- `src/modules/infra/types.ts` — Add `observabilityBackend` to `InitOptions`. +1 line. Target: ~137 lines.\n   192→- `src/lib/state.ts` — Add `backend` field to `otlp` interface, default in `getDefaultState()`, backfill in `migrateState()`. +5 lines. Target: ~298 lines.\n   193→- `src/modules/infra/init-project.ts` — Store `opts.observabilityBackend` in state, handle `'none'` backend. +8 lines. Target: ~244 lines.\n   194→- `src/modules/infra/docker-setup.ts` — Select compose file based on backend choice in `handleLocalShared()`. +5 lines. Target: ~304 lines (may need extraction).\n   195→- `src/modules/status/formatters.ts` — Backend-aware Docker check dispatch in `handleDockerCheck()` and `handleFullStatus()`. +15 lines. Already at 574 (pre-existing violation).\n   196→- `templates/docker-compose.elk.yml` — New file. OpenSearch + Dashboards + OTel Collector compose. ~50 lines.\n   197→- `src/modules/infra/__tests__/docker-setup.test.ts` — Add backend-aware compose selection tests.\n   198→- `src/modules/infra/__tests__/init-project.test.ts` — Add `--observability-backend` option tests.\n   199→\n   200→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-START:story-verification -->\n   201→## Verification Requirements\n   202→\n   203→- [ ] Showboat proof document created (`docs/exec-plans/active/14-4-observability-backend-choice.proof.md`)\n   204→- [ ] All acceptance criteria verified with real-world evidence\n   205→- [ ] Test coverage meets target (100%)\n   206→\n   207→## Documentation Requirements\n   208→\n   209→- [ ] Relevant AGENTS.md files updated (list modules touched)\n   210→- [ ] Exec-plan created in `docs/exec-plans/active/14-4-observability-backend-choice.md`\n   211→\n   212→## Testing Requirements\n   213→\n   214→- [ ] Unit tests written for all new/changed code\n   215→- [ ] Integration tests for cross-module interactions\n   216→- [ ] Coverage target: 100%\n   217→<!-- CODEHARNESS-PATCH-END:story-verification -->\n   218→\n   219→## Dev Agent Record\n   220→\n   221→### Agent Model Used\n   222→\n   223→Claude Opus 4.6 (1M context)\n   224→\n   225→### Debug Log References\n   226→\n   227→### Completion Notes List\n   228→\n   229→- All 14 tasks completed. Build passes. All 3683 vitest tests and 307 BATS tests pass.\n   230→- `docker-setup.ts` is at exactly 300 lines (1 line over pre-story 299). Minimal change.\n   231→- `formatters.ts` grew from 574 to 597 lines (23 lines added for backend-aware checks). Exempt per AC 10.\n   232→- Added `writeState` call before Docker setup to persist backend choice even if Docker setup fails.\n   233→\n   234→### Change Log\n   235→\n   236→- 2026-03-25: Story created with 10 ACs (3 from epic, 7 derived from architecture analysis, existing code audit, testing, and line-limit enforcement). Full implementation guidance with file locations, line budgets, current-state assessment, and anti-patterns. Status set to ready-for-dev.\n   237→- 2026-03-25: All tasks implemented. Added `--observability-backend` CLI option, `otlp.backend` state field, backend-aware Docker health checks, ELK compose template, and unit tests. Status set to review.\n   238→\n   239→### File List\n   240→\n   241→- `src/commands/init.ts` — Added `--observability-backend` CLI option (+3 lines)\n   242→- `src/modules/infra/types.ts` — Added `observabilityBackend` to `InitOptions` (+1 line)\n   243→- `src/lib/state.ts` — Added `backend` field to otlp interface, backfill in migrateState (+5 lines)\n   244→- `src/modules/infra/init-project.ts` — Store backend choice, handle 'none' backend early return (+21 lines)\n   245→- `src/modules/infra/docker-setup.ts` — Select compose file based on backend (+2 lines)\n   246→- `src/modules/status/formatters.ts` — Backend-aware Docker checks in handleDockerCheck, handleFullStatus, handleHealthCheck (+23 lines)\n   247→- `src/lib/stack-path.ts` — Added `getElkComposeFilePath()` (+4 lines)\n   248→- `templates/docker-compose.elk.yml` — New: OpenSearch + Dashboards + OTel Collector compose (58 lines)\n   249→- `src/modules/infra/__tests__/docker-setup.test.ts` — Added backend-aware compose selection tests\n   250→- `src/modules/infra/__tests__/init-project.test.ts` — Added `--observability-backend` option tests\n   251→- `src/modules/status/__tests__/formatters-docker-check.test.ts` — New: backend-aware Docker check tests\n   252→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_013rWcam9ZLGWy8y97T6yhWS","session_id":"790cd04c-5c91-45bb-998d-78a56b65af9a","uuid":"68a59178-4a66-4d0b-a78b-93dd0576c147","timestamp":"2026-03-24T23:16:29.269Z"}
