{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_013rWcam9ZLGWy8y97T6yhWS","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Build passes. 3692 tests pass (9 new). Coverage at 97.08%, all files above 80%.\n\n---\n\n**CODE REVIEW FINDINGS**\n\n**Story:** `_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/14-4-observability-backend-choice.md`\n**Issues Found:** 1 High, 3 Medium, 3 Low\n**Issues Fixed:** 1 High, 3 Medium (all HIGH and MEDIUM fixed)\n\n**HIGH issues (fixed):**\n1. **Missing CLI validation for `--observability-backend`** — `init.ts:52` uses unsafe `as` cast; a user passing `--observability-backend foobar` would store an invalid value in state. Fixed by adding validation in `initProjectInner()` with a clear error message.\n\n**MEDIUM issues (fixed):**\n2. **ELK compose file resolution in `formatters.ts`** — `handleFullStatus`, `handleFullStatusJson`, `handleDockerCheck`, and `handleHealthCheck` all resolved shared compose files to `getComposeFilePath()` (Victoria) regardless of backend. When `backend === 'elk'`, `getStackHealth` was called with the wrong file. Fixed by adding `resolveSharedCompose()` helper that dispatches to `getElkComposeFilePath()` for ELK.\n3. **Victoria-specific endpoints shown for ELK** — `DEFAULT_ENDPOINTS` (ports 9428/8428/16686) were displayed even when backend was `elk` (which uses port 9200). Fixed by adding `ELK_ENDPOINTS` and `getDefaultEndpointsForBackend()`, used throughout formatters.\n4. **`resolveEndpoints()` not backend-aware** — Always returned `DEFAULT_ENDPOINTS` for local-shared, regardless of backend. Fixed to check `state.otlp.backend` and return appropriate endpoints.\n\n**Files modified by review fixes:**\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/infra/init-project.ts` — backend validation\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/status/formatters.ts` — compose resolution + endpoint fixes\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/status/endpoints.ts` — `ELK_ENDPOINTS`, `getDefaultEndpointsForBackend()`\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/infra/__tests__/init-project.test.ts` — invalid backend test\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/status/__tests__/formatters-docker-check.test.ts` — ELK compose + endpoints tests\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/status/__tests__/endpoints.test.ts` — ELK endpoint tests\n\nStory status updated to `verifying`.\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found and their severity:**\n- **HIGH**: Missing CLI validation for `--observability-backend` — unsafe `as` cast allows arbitrary strings to bypass TypeScript and persist in state. Fixed.\n- **MEDIUM**: ELK compose file resolution — all four formatter functions (`handleFullStatus`, `handleFullStatusJson`, `handleDockerCheck`, `handleHealthCheck`) resolved shared compose path to Victoria compose even for ELK backend. Fixed.\n- **MEDIUM**: Wrong endpoints displayed for ELK — Victoria-specific ports (9428/8428/16686) shown instead of OpenSearch ports (9200). Fixed.\n- **MEDIUM**: `resolveEndpoints()` not backend-aware — always returned Victoria defaults for local-shared regardless of backend. Fixed.\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW priority items, tech debt):**\n- `--no-observability` combined with `--observability-backend none` has subtly different semantics (the `none` path persists `backend: 'none'` in state; `--no-observability` alone does not set `backend`). Inconsistency could confuse downstream consumers.\n- `formatters.ts` at 605 lines — pre-existing 300-line violation, now worse. Needs decomposition into sub-modules (Docker checks, sprint state, beads).\n- `docker-setup.ts` at exactly 300 lines — at the limit, fragile for future changes.\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- No integration tests for the full `codeharness init --observability-backend elk` CLI flow end-to-end.\n- `handleFullStatus` and `handleFullStatusJson` ELK local-shared branches have no direct test coverage (covered indirectly via `handleDockerCheck` tests).\n- `handleHealthCheck` ELK branch not directly tested (only the compose resolution was fixed; no dedicated test added for the health check ELK path).\n- Missing proof document at `docs/exec-plans/active/14-4-observability-backend-choice.proof.md`.\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- `DEFAULT_ENDPOINTS` vs `ELK_ENDPOINTS` pattern will need extension if a third backend is added. Consider a map keyed by backend type.\n- `buildScopedEndpoints()` in `endpoints.ts` uses Victoria-specific URL patterns (VictoriaLogs query syntax, VictoriaMetrics PromQL, Jaeger API). These are meaningless for ELK — OpenSearch uses `_search` API, not `/select/logsql/query`. The scoped endpoints for ELK are currently wrong but this is out of scope for this story.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None. All HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed. Story is in `verifying` status."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a76de930cde997044 (use SendMessage with to: 'a76de930cde997044' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 103242\ntool_uses: 85\nduration_ms: 460786</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"790cd04c-5c91-45bb-998d-78a56b65af9a","uuid":"749a225d-2789-4acd-bd7c-b6e7aa1aab52","timestamp":"2026-03-24T23:24:06.626Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-code-review for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/14-4-observability-backend-choice.md — perform adversarial review, fix all HIGH and MEDIUM issues found. After fixing, run `codeharness coverage --min-file 80` and ensure all files pass the per-file floor and the overall 90% target. Update the story status to `verifying` when all issues are fixed and coverage passes. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response with a `## Session Issues` section listing:\n- Bugs found and their severity (HIGH/MEDIUM/LOW with brief des