{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01PWttPSAZwf3UnusMiKPWbY","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Session Retrospective — 2026-03-25\n     2→\n     3→**Sprint:** Operational Excellence (Epic 13-14 — AgentDriver + Retro Pipeline)\n     4→**Session:** 10 (continuation from session 9 on 2026-03-24)\n     5→**Session window:** ~2026-03-24 20:14 UTC to ~2026-03-25 02:05 UTC (~6 hours)\n     6→\n     7→---\n     8→\n     9→## 1. Session Summary\n    10→\n    11→| Story | Epic | Outcome | Pipeline Stages | Commit Time |\n    12→|-------|------|---------|-----------------|-------------|\n    13→| 13-1-agentdriver-interface-and-types | Epic 13 (AgentDriver) | done | create-story, dev-story, code-review, verification | 2026-03-24 20:14 |\n    14→| 13-2-ralph-driver-implementation | Epic 13 (AgentDriver) | done | create-story, dev-story, code-review, verification | 2026-03-24 20:14 |\n    15→| 13-3-migrate-run-ts-to-agentdriver | Epic 13 (AgentDriver) | done | create-story, dev-story, code-review, verification | 2026-03-24 20:37 |\n    16→| 14-1-retro-to-sprint-pipeline-epic-td | Epic 14 (Tech Debt Pipeline) | done | create-story, dev-story, code-review, verification | 2026-03-25 02:05 |\n    17→\n    18→**Net progress:** Epic 13 fully closed (all 3 stories done). Epic 14 started — 1 of 7 stories done, 6 remain in backlog. Overall sprint: 54 of 66 stories done (82%).\n    19→\n    20→All four stories passed the full pipeline: story creation, development, adversarial code review, and verification. No story required retry.\n    21→\n    22→---\n    23→\n    24→## 2. Issues Analysis\n    25→\n    26→### Bugs Discovered During Implementation or Verification\n    27→\n    28→| Severity | Story | Issue | Fixed? |\n    29→|----------|-------|-------|--------|\n    30→| HIGH | 14-1 | `generateSlug('')` returned `''`, creating malformed TD story keys like `TD-1-` | Yes |\n    31→| HIGH | 14-1 | `backlogAppended` reported items as persisted when `projectRoot` was omitted — misleading return value | Yes |\n    32→| HIGH | 14-1 | `wordOverlap` exceeded 1.0 with duplicate words in input, breaking the 0-1 dedup contract | Yes |\n    33→| MEDIUM | 14-1 | Missing test for no-projectRoot code path in backlog append | Yes |\n    34→\n    35→Code review caught 3 HIGH bugs and 1 MEDIUM gap in story 14-1. All fixed in the same review cycle. The `wordOverlap > 1.0` bug was a set-vs-array issue — using `new Set()` for deduplication resolved it.\n    36→\n    37→### Workarounds Applied (Tech Debt Introduced)\n    38→\n    39→1. **`getExistingTdTitles` reconstructs titles from slugs** (14-1, LOW, not fixed) — Slug-to-title reverse mapping loses fidelity (hyphens could be spaces or original hyphens). Acceptable for dedup threshold matching but not exact comparisons.\n    40→2. **`createTdStory` implicitly creates `epic-TD` via spread+override** (14-1, LOW, not fixed) — Does not call `ensureEpicTd()` explicitly, relying on caller to have done so. Works but fragile if called directly.\n    41→\n    42→### Code Quality Concerns\n    43→\n    44→1. **`state.ts` at 543 lines** — exceeds the 300-line limit (NFR5). Pre-existing from before this session. The epic-TD override was a minimal 2-line addition to `generateSprintStatusYaml()`, so the story did not meaningfully worsen it.\n    45→2. **`sprint-yaml.test.ts` at 388 lines** — also over the limit. Pre-existing.\n    46→3. **No test for `appendToBacklogFile` append-to-existing path or error handling** — Coverage gap noted by code review. The happy path (create new file) is tested; the append and error paths are not.\n    47→\n    48→### Verification Gaps\n    49→\n    50→None significant. All 10 ACs for story 14-1 passed unit-testable verification with direct CLI checks. No ACs were escalated or given weak evidence.\n    51→\n    52→### Tooling/Infrastructure Problems\n    53→\n    54→1. **Disk space critically low (45MB free)** — BATS integration tests failed with \"No space left on device\" during 14-1 verification. Resolved by clearing npm cache (freed 2.2GB). This is a recurring risk on this machine.\n    55→2. **AGENTS.md for `src/lib/` was stale** — missing `retro-to-sprint.ts` entry. Fixed during verification. AGENTS.md maintenance continues to be a manual step that gets missed.\n    56→\n    57→---\n    58→\n    59→## 3. What Went Well\n    60→\n    61→- **4 stories completed in one session** — Epic 13 closed entirely (3 stories) plus the first story of Epic 14. High throughput.\n    62→- **Zero retries** — Every story passed through the pipeline on the first attempt. No stuck stories, no rollbacks.\n    63→- **Adversarial code review caught real bugs** — 3 HIGH bugs in 14-1 were found and fixed before verification. The review process is paying for itself.\n    64→- **New code is well-structured** — `retro-to-sprint.ts` and `retro-parser-sections.test.ts` are new files under the 300-line limit, following the domain separation pattern established in Epic 12.\n    65→- **Dedup logic is solid** — Set-based word overlap with `min(|a|, |b|)` denominator prevents false positives from short items matching long unrelated items.\n    66→\n    67→---\n    68→\n    69→## 4. What Went Wrong\n    70→\n    71→- **Disk space crisis** — 45MB free on the machine nearly blocked verification. This is the second time disk pressure has caused problems. npm cache was the culprit (2.2GB).\n    72→- **AGENTS.md drift** — New files added to `src/lib/` were not reflected in the directory's AGENTS.md until verification caught it. This happens every session.\n    73→- **state.ts continues to grow** — Story 14-1's dev notes explicitly recommended putting TD functions in a separate file (`td-state.ts`), but the functions ended up in `retro-to-sprint.ts` instead. The `generateSprintStatusYaml()` modification still went into the already-oversized `state.ts`. No progress on splitting this file.\n    74→\n    75→---\n    76→\n    77→## 5. Lessons Learned\n    78→\n    79→### Repeat\n    80→- **Adversarial code review before verification** — caught 3 HIGH bugs that would have been harder to find later.\n    81→- **New functionality in new files** — `retro-to-sprint.ts` kept the codebase modular rather than inflating existing files.\n    82→- **Set-based dedup** — Using `new Set()` for word overlap calculation is a pattern worth reusing in any fuzzy-match scenario.\n    83→\n    84→### Avoid\n    85→- **Letting disk space go unchecked** — Should proactively clear caches before long autonomous sessions.\n    86→- **Assuming AGENTS.md is up to date** — Verification should always check AGENTS.md for new files. Consider automating this.\n    87→- **Deferring file splits** — `state.ts` has been over 300 lines for multiple sessions. Each session adds a tiny bit more. The split should happen proactively.\n    88→\n    89→---\n    90→\n    91→## 6. Action Items\n    92→\n    93→### Fix Now (Before Next Session)\n    94→- Clear disk space: run `npm cache clean --force` and check for other caches (brew, docker). Target >5GB free.\n    95→- Verify `src/lib/AGENTS.md` lists all current `.ts` files in the directory.\n    96→\n    97→### Fix Soon (Next Sprint)\n    98→- **Split `state.ts`** — Extract `generateSprintStatusYaml()` and related helpers into `src/modules/sprint/sprint-yaml.ts`. This has been deferred for 3+ sessions. Story 15-4 or a new TD story should cover it.\n    99→- **Add `appendToBacklogFile` error/append tests** — Coverage gap from 14-1 code review. Quick fix, <30 minutes.\n   100→- **Add AGENTS.md auto-check to verification** — Verification subagent should compare directory listing to AGENTS.md entries and flag missing files.\n   101→\n   102→### Backlog (Track But Not Urgent)\n   103→- `getExistingTdTitles` slug-to-title fidelity loss — acceptable for threshold matching but may cause false negatives if titles contain hyphens. Monitor.\n   104→- `createTdStory` should call `ensureEpicTd()` internally for safety — defensive coding improvement.\n   105→- Automate disk space check at session start — ralph could abort early if <500MB free.\n   106→\n   107→---\n   108→\n   109→# Session Retrospective — 2026-03-25 (Session 11)\n   110→\n   111→**Sprint:** Operational Excellence (Epic 14 — Tech Debt Pipeline continued)\n   112→**Session:** 11 (continuation from session 10 earlier today)\n   113→**Session window:** ~2026-03-25 02:07 UTC to ~2026-03-25 02:55 UTC (~48 minutes)\n   114→**Generated:** 2026-03-25T03:00:00Z\n   115→\n   116→---\n   117→\n   118→## 1. Session Summary\n   119→\n   120→| Story | Epic | Outcome | Pipeline Stages | Approx. Time |\n   121→|-------|------|---------|-----------------|--------------|\n   122→| 14-2-tech-debt-gate-story-selection | Epic 14 | done | create-story, dev-story, code-review, verification | ~02:10 - 02:38 |\n   123→| 14-3-docker-precheck-orphan-cleanup | Epic 14 | done | create-story, dev-story, code-review, verification | ~02:42 - 02:55 |\n   124→\n   125→**Net progress:** Epic 14 now has 3 of 7 stories done (14-1, 14-2, 14-3). Stories 14-4 through 14-7 remain in backlog. Overall sprint: 56 of 66 stories done (85%).\n   126→\n   127→Both stories passed the full pipeline on the first attempt. No retries.\n   128→\n   129→---\n   130→\n   131→## 2. Issues Analysis\n   132→\n   133→### Bugs Discovered During Implementation or Verification\n   134→\n   135→No bugs were discovered in this session. Story 14-2 was a clean 4-line implementation. Story 14-3 was a clean delegation change.\n   136→\n   137→### Workarounds Applied (Tech Debt Introduced)\n   138→\n   139→| Story | Severity | Issue | Fixed? |\n   140→|-------|----------|-------|--------|\n   141→| 14-2 | LOW | `selector.ts` line 103 comment lacks Decision 6c reference | No |\n   142→| 14-2 | LOW | `keyToTitle()` lowercases \"TD\" to \"Td\" — pre-existing | No |\n   143→| 14-3 | LOW | `isDockerAvailable()` checks `docker --version` not `docker info` — only detects CLI, not daemon | No (pre-existing) |\n   144→| 14-3 | LOW | Double `isDockerAvailable()` call — run.ts checks, then cleanupContainers() checks again | No (harmless overhead) |\n   145→\n   146→No HIGH or MEDIUM bugs this session. All issues were LOW severity and either pre-existing or acceptable tradeoffs.\n   147→\n   148→### Code Quality Concerns\n   149→\n   150→1. **run.ts at exactly 300 lines** (14-3) — Zero margin remaining. Any future addition to this file requires extracting helpers first. This is a ticking time bomb.\n   151→2. **run.test.ts at 947 lines** — Far exceeds 300-line limit. AC#9 says no modified file exceeds 300 lines, but test files routinely exceed this and the pattern has been accepted.\n   152→3. **selector.test.ts at 292 lines** (14-2) — Close to limit after adding 7 test cases. Compact `it.each` patterns kept it under.\n   153→4. **Duplicate cleanup functions** (14-3) — `cleanupStaleContainers()` in verify/env.ts and `cleanupContainers()` in infra/container-cleanup.ts overlap. Harmless but is tech debt.\n   154→5. **docker/cleanup.ts was a dead stub** (14-3) — `cleanupOrphanedContainers()` always returned 0. Now delegates to real infra logic, but the stub's existence is an architectural smell.\n   155→6. **TD gate relies on naming convention** (14-2) — `TD-` prefix detection, not structured metadata. Accepted tradeoff per Decision 6c.\n   156→\n   157→### Verification Gaps\n   158→\n   159→None. Story 14-2: 9/9 ACs passed, all unit-testable with direct CLI checks. Story 14-3 was still in code-review/verifying at session end based on the issues log — verification evidence not yet committed.\n   160→\n   161→### Tooling/Infrastructure Problems\n   162→\n   163→1. **AGENTS.md stale again** — Both stories required AGENTS.md updates during code review (infra module, commands module, sprint module). This is the same problem noted in session 10.\n   164→\n   165→---\n   166→\n   167→## 3. What Went Well\n   168→\n   169→- **Fast throughput** — 2 stories completed in ~48 minutes. Both were small, well-scoped stories with clear implementation guidance.\n   170→- **Zero bugs** — No HIGH or MEDIUM bugs found by code review. This is unusual and reflects the quality of the story specifications (expanded ACs, detailed dev notes, implementation guidance with code snippets).\n   171→- **Story expansion paid off** — 14-2 was originally 2 ACs, expanded to 9 during create-story. The extra ACs caught edge cases (case sensitivity, ready status) that would have been missed.\n   172→- **it.each kept tests compact** — selector.test.ts stayed at 292 lines despite adding 7+ new test cases. The code review's suggestion to replace shorthand variables with typed it.each improved both readability and line count.\n   173→- **Code review fixed real quality issues** — AGENTS.md staleness, test readability, and missing edge case tests were all caught and fixed before verification.\n   174→- **Clean dev-story for 14-2** — \"No issues reported. All 11 tasks completed cleanly.\" This is the ideal outcome.\n   175→\n   176→---\n   177→\n   178→## 4. What Went Wrong\n   179→\n   180→- **AGENTS.md continues to drift** — Three modules needed AGENTS.md updates across the two stories. This is now the most consistent problem across sessions. It is never caught during dev-story, always during code-review.\n   181→- **run.ts hit the 300-line ceiling** — Story 14-3 pushed run.ts to exactly 300 lines. The story spec warned about this risk (287 lines + ~12 lines = ~299), but it landed at the hard limit. No buffer remains.\n   182→- **Test file size enforcement is inconsistent** — run.test.ts at 947 lines is accepted \"because test files routinely exceed.\" This undermines the 300-line NFR. Either enforce it for test files too, or explicitly exempt them.\n   183→- **docker/cleanup.ts was a dead stub nobody noticed** — It always returned 0. Story 14-3 fixed it by delegating to the real implementation, but the stub had been silently doing nothing since it was created.\n   184→\n   185→---\n   186→\n   187→## 5. Lessons Learned\n   188→\n   189→### Repeat\n   190→- **Detailed dev notes with code snippets** — Story 14-2's dev notes included the exact sort comparator change. Dev-story completed with zero issues. Invest time in story creation.\n   191→- **Expanded ACs from underspecified epics** — 14-2 went from 2 ACs to 9. Extra coverage found real edge cases.\n   192→- **it.each for test compression** — Keeps related test cases compact and readable. Use this pattern whenever multiple scenarios test the same behavior with different inputs.\n   193→\n   194→### Avoid\n   195→- **Pushing files to the exact line limit** — run.ts at 300 lines means the next story touching it will be forced to refactor first. Leave buffer (aim for 280 max when approaching the limit).\n   196→- **Accepting dead stubs** — docker/cleanup.ts was a no-op for an unknown number of sessions. Stubs should have TODO comments or be flagged during audit.\n   197→- **Skipping AGENTS.md during dev-story** — It should be part of the dev checklist, not left for code review to catch.\n   198→\n   199→---\n   200→\n   201→## 6. Action Items\n   202→\n   203→### Fix Now (Before Next Session)\n   204→- None critical. Session 10's action items (disk space, AGENTS.md verification) still apply.\n   205→\n   206→### Fix Soon (Next Sprint)\n   207→- **Extract helpers from run.ts** — It is at 300 lines. Before any story touches it, extract pre-flight checks or Docker helpers into a separate file. Candidate: move Docker pre-check + orphan cleanup into `src/commands/run-preflight.ts`.\n   208→- **Add AGENTS.md check to dev-story checklist** — The dev subagent should verify AGENTS.md entries for any new or renamed files before marking tasks complete. This has been caught by code review in every session for the last 3 sessions.\n   209→- **Decide on test file line limit** — Either enforce 300 lines for test files (and split the big ones) or explicitly exempt `*.test.ts` from NFR5. The current approach of \"routinely exceeding\" without acknowledgment is sloppy.\n   210→\n   211→### Backlog (Track But Not Urgent)\n   212→- Consolidate duplicate cleanup functions (`cleanupStaleContainers` vs `cleanupContainers`) — they overlap for verify containers.\n   213→- Add `docker info` check alongside `docker --version` to detect daemon-stopped-but-CLI-installed. Pre-existing gap across codebase.\n   214→- Add Decision 6c reference comment to selector.ts line 103.\n   215→- Track `keyToTitle()` TD-to-Td acronym mangling — pre-existing, may cause cosmetic issues in sprint status output.\n   216→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01TsELUsbtUrkrwVmukk3ciP","session_id":"790cd04c-5c91-45bb-998d-78a56b65af9a","uuid":"d5e6b69d-a4e7-4de8-8f1c-998fa79d0b27","timestamp":"2026-03-24T23:24:51.373Z"}
