ted, their outcomes, time spent\n2. **Issues analysis** — categorize and analyze all issues from the session log:\n   - Bugs discovered during implementation or verification\n   - Workarounds applied (tech debt introduced this session)\n   - Code quality concerns raised by reviewers\n   - Verification gaps (escalated ACs, weak evidence)\n   - Tooling/infrastructure problems (sandbox, permissions, CLI issues)\n3. **What went well** — stories completed, bugs fixed, process improvements\n4. **What went wrong** — failures, blockers, stuck stories, wasted iterations\n5. **Lessons learned** — patterns to repeat or avoid\n6. **Action items** — concrete next steps, split into:\n   - Fix now (before next session)\n   - Fix soon (next sprint)\n   - Backlog (track but not urgent)\n\nWrite the retrospective to _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-03-25.md where the date is today's date in YYYY-MM-DD format.\n\nIf a session retro for today already exists, append to it with a `---` separator and timestamp.\n\nDo NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously.\nDo NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.","agentId":"a0a9a22e423c3ccd8","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Retrospective for session 12 appended to `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-2026-03-25.md`.\n\n**Summary of what was written:**\n\n- **Session 12** covers story 14-4 (observability-backend-choice), currently in \"verifying\" state\n- **4 bugs caught by code review** — 1 HIGH (missing CLI validation for `--observability-backend`), 3 MEDIUM (ELK compose/endpoint resolution all pointing at Victoria)\n- **Key concern:** formatters.ts grew to 605 lines; docker-setup.ts hit exactly 300 lines — two more files at or past the ceiling\n- **Cross-session trends section added** tracking patterns across all three sessions today: AGENTS.md staleness, 300-line ceiling hits, formatters.ts unbounded growth, code revie